description: On the eve of Kate's (Mamrie Hart) 30th birthday, friends Evie (Grace Helbig) and Charlie (Hannah Hart) offer to throw her a party. But the celebration quickly spirals out of control.

title: Stuart Little 2
cast: Geena Davis, Michael J. Fox, Hugh Laurie, Nathan Lane, Jonathan Lipnicki, Melanie Griffith, James Woods, Steve Zahn, Rachael Harris
description: The brave and pint-sized hero Stuart Little (Michael J. Fox) returns in Stuart Little 2, delightingaudiences with his big heart and even more action-packed adventure. This time, Stuart must journey through the city with reluctant Snowbell (Nathan Lane) to rescue a new friend, Margalo (Melanie Griffith), from a villainous Falcon (James Woods).

title: Experimenter
cast: Peter Sarsgaard, Winona Ryder, Jim Gaffigan, Edoardo Ballerini, Kellan Lutz, Dennis Haysbert, Danny Abeckaser, Taryn Manning, Anton Yelchin
description: Stanley Milgram (Peter Sarsgaard) conducts an experiment in which people think they're delivering electric shocks to strangers. Ignoring pleas for mercy, most subjects don't stop because they've been told to go on. With Winona Ryder and Jim Gaffigan.

title: Cinderella
cast: Camila Cabello
description: From Kay Cannon (Pitch Perfect), Cinderella is a modern movie musical with a bold take on the classic fairytale. Our ambitious heroine (Camila Cabello) has big dreams and with the help of her Fab Godmother, she perseveres to make them come true. Cinderella has an all-star cast including Idina Menzel, Minnie Driver, James Corden, Nicholas Galitzine, Billy Porter and Pierce Brosnan.

title: Irish Jam
cast: Dudley Sutton, Eddie Griffith, Anna Friel
description: Upon discovering that their town is up for sale, crafty Irish villagers scheme to raise the money to prevent the buy-out. They hold a poetry contest with a tempting grand prize – the deed to their local pub. But what could happen when a duplicitous American rapper emerges as the best poet around?

title: An American Girl Story: Summer Camp, Friends For Life
cast: Zoe Manarel, Alison Fernandez, Lauren Donzis, Camryn Manheim, Monique Green
description: Aspiring filmmaker, Z and Paz, a budding engineer, arrive at S.T.E.A.M. camp excited for tech heaven. When the administrator makes them explore nature and confiscates all tech, they think their summer’s doomed. Things take a mysterious turn when they meet Jordan, an enchanting “counselor” who sends them on an adventure, opening them up to a world of possibilities – like befriending Drew.

title: The Grudge 2
cast: Amber Tamblyn, Arielle Kebbel, Jennifer Beals, Edison Chen, Sarah Roemer, Sarah Michelle Gellar
description: Acclaimed producers Sam Raimi, Rob Tapert and Taka Ichise have re-teamed with director Takashi Shimizu and screenwriter Stephen Susco to present this heart-stopping sequel to the smash-hit thriller, The Grudge.

title: Stargate
cast: Kurt Russell, James Spader, Jaye Davidson, Viveca Lindfors, John Diehl
description: When an ancient Egyptian artifact is discovered, two men unlock its secret power as a portal through time and space.

title: If You Give a Mouse a Cookie
cast: Mason Mahay, Roger Craig Smith, Jessica DiCiccio, Jeff Bennett, Lara Jill Miller, Henry Kaufman, Kyla Kenedy White, Scarlet Estevez, Benji Risley
description: If You Give A Mouse A Cookie, Series: Based on the beloved books by Laura Numeroff and Felicia Bond. Meet Mouse, Pig, Moose, Dog and Cat and their favorite kids! When everyone gets together one thing always leads to another in the most unexpected ways. You never know where things will end up, but you can be sure that IF Mouse and Friends go on an adventure, THEN there is lots of fun to be had!

title: Bride Wars
cast: Kate Hudson, Anne Hathaway, Kristen Johnston, Bryan Greenberg, Candice Bergen
description: When a clerical error causes a clash in wedding dates, two best friends who'd do anything for each other find themselves in a no-holds-barred, take-no-prisoners struggle that threatens to erupt into all-out war.

title: What Happens in Vegas
cast: Cameron Diaz,  Ashton Kutcher,  Rob Corddry,  Lake Bell
description: Jack Fuller (Ashton Kutcher) and Joy McNally (Cameron Diaz) are two strangers who awaken together to discover they've gotten married following a night of debauchery in Sin City... and one of them has won a huge jackpot after playing the other's quarter.

title: Marley & Me
cast: Owen Wilson, Jennifer Aniston
description: Jennifer Aniston and Owen Wilson unleash huge laughs as John and Jenny Grogan, a young couple contemplating the decision to have a baby. Then came Marley...an adorable Labrador pup who flunks obedience school and quickly turns his new home into a disaster area. But over the years, the Grogans come to realize that "the world's worst dog" truly brings out the best in them.
